[SN]TITLE[SN]
Richard Bernard murder: Teenager sentenced to life

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A teenager who stabbed a man to death at his home has been jailed for life with a minimum of 18 years.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Richard Bernard, 51, was found injured outside his flat on Trocadero Court in Derby on 24 May and died shortly after.
Mohammed Ibrahim, 19, of no fixed address, was sentenced after pleading guilty to murder at Nottingham Crown Court in December.
The court was told the killer never explained why he had attacked his victim.
Mr Bernard's mother Nita, sister Claire and brother Andrew said previously they were "devastated" by his death and he had been a "very much-loved son and brother".
